<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-47-0311 </DOCNO><TEXT>The success of energy from biomass still depends on whether machines forharvesting biomass can be developed. However, present energy prices andrecent experience call for some rethinking on the question of what forminnovation incentives should take. Forms must be found which involvefewer risks for manufacturers who wish to continue innovating. Cooperationbetween technical research centres and manufacturers would seem to beone of the factors of success. Another is the amount and type of aidgranted to firms.</TEXT></DOC>